SIMPLE: faintness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Faintness
<hw>Faint"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being
faint; loss of strength, or of consciousness, and
self-control.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Want of vigor or energy.</def>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Feebleness, as of color or light; lack of
distinctness; <as>as, <ex>faintness</ex> of description</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Faint-heartedness; timorousness;
dejection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will send a <qex>faintness</qex> into their hearts.</q>
<rj><qau>Lev. xxvi. 36.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Faints</ent>⟦br⟧
